In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims March 2013 as American Red Cross Month. He acknowledges the commitment and service of the American Red Cross in providing relief to communities around the world. He highlights the organization's founding by Clara Barton in 1881 and their efforts to assist those affected by civil war and natural disasters. The President also commends the American Red Cross for their response to Hurricane Sandy, where professionals and volunteers worked tirelessly to provide supplies and shelter to those in need. He emphasizes the importance of unity and service in times of hardship and encourages Americans to support service and relief organizations.